In[11]:
def haversine(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2):
    R = 6371  # Earth radius in kilometres
    lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2 = map(np.radians, [lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2])
    dlat = lat2 - lat1
    dlon = lon2 - lon1
    a = np.sin(dlat/2.0)**2 + np.cos(lat1) * np.cos(lat2) * np.sin(dlon/2.0)**2
    c = 2 * np.arcsin(np.sqrt(a))
    return R * c

df['Distance_km'] = haversine(
    df['Store_Latitude'], df['Store_Longitude'],
    df['Drop_Latitude'], df['Drop_Longitude']
)

features.append('Distance_km')

df_weekly = df.groupby(pd.Grouper(key='Order_Date', freq='W'))['Delivery_Time'].mean().reset_index()
real_mean = df_weekly['Delivery_Time'].mean()
real_std = df_weekly['Delivery_Time'].std()
In[33]:
#To Simulate 104 weeks (2 years)
weeks = pd.date_range(start='2022-01-01', periods=104, freq='W')
In[34]:
# To create pattern using real mean, std, and sinusoidal seasonality
np.random.seed(42)
trend = np.linspace(real_mean - 5, real_mean + 5, 104)
seasonality = 4 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * np.arange(104) / 52)  # annual pattern
noise = np.random.normal(0, real_std, 104)
simulated = trend + seasonality + noise
df_dummy = pd.DataFrame({'ds': weeks, 'y': simulated})

if 'sarima_result' in locals():
    residuals = sarima_result.resid.dropna().reset_index()
    residuals['time_idx'] = np.arange(len(residuals))
    X_hybrid = residuals[['time_idx']]
    y_hybrid = residuals['resid']

    hybrid_model = XGBRegressor(random_state=42)
    hybrid_model.fit(X_hybrid, y_hybrid)

    future_idx = pd.DataFrame({'time_idx': np.arange(len(residuals), len(residuals)+6)})
    future_residuals = hybrid_model.predict(future_idx)

# Preparing weekly aggregated time series
df_week = df.groupby(pd.Grouper(key='Order_Date', freq='W'))['Delivery_Time'].mean().reset_index()
df_week = df_week.rename(columns={'Order_Date':'Week', 'Delivery_Time':'Avg_Delivery_Time'})

# SARIMA model fitting and forecasting 4 weeks ahead
model = SARIMAX(df_week.set_index('Week')['Avg_Delivery_Time'], order=(1,1,1), seasonal_order=(1,1,1,52))
results = model.fit(disp=False)
forecast = results.get_forecast(steps=4)
forecast_index = forecast.row_labels  # future week indices
forecast_mean = forecast.predicted_mean
forecast_ci = forecast.conf_int()

# Plotting SARIMA forecast vs actual
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
plt.plot(df_week['Week'], df_week['Avg_Delivery_Time'], label='Actual', marker='o')
plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast_mean, label='Forecast', marker='x')
plt.fill_between(forecast_index, forecast_ci.iloc[:,0], forecast_ci.iloc[:,1], color='gray', alpha=0.3, label='95% CI')
plt.title('SARIMA Forecast of Weekly Average Delivery Time')
plt.xlabel('Week'); plt.ylabel('Average Delivery Time (minutes)')
plt.legend(); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()

# Prophet model fitting and forecasting 6 weeks ahead
prophet_df = df_week.rename(columns={'Week':'ds','Avg_Delivery_Time':'y'})
prophet_model = Prophet(yearly_seasonality=True, weekly_seasonality=True, daily_seasonality=False)
prophet_model.fit(prophet_df)
future = prophet_model.make_future_dataframe(periods=6, freq='W')
forecast_df = prophet_model.predict(future)

# Plotting Prophet forecast
fig = prophet_model.plot(forecast_df, xlabel='Week', ylabel='Avg Delivery Time (minutes)')
plt.title('Prophet Forecast  Weekly Delivery Time'); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()

Conclusion

This successfully applied a hybrid framework of machine learning and time-series forecasting techniques to analyse seasonal trends and predict delivery efficiency in e-commerce logistics using the Amazon Delivery Dataset. Key insights include:

SARIMA initially failed on monthly data due to limited observations but performed well after switching to weekly granularity.

Prophet effectively captured seasonal patterns and can be further enhanced using holiday regressors and additional features such as weather and traffic.

Machine learning models, including regression and classification approaches, provided useful predictions regarding delivery times and regional performance.

These findings demonstrate the potential of combining statistical and machine learning methods for real-world logistics optimisation. Future improvements could involve deploying the model in a real-time environment and incorporating external datasets for higher predictive power.
